{
  "text": "The VG mode controlled the mean V Te within 3% of the set V Te for triggered and untriggered inflations. There was a large variation in V Te . This was due to: (a) infants suddenly taking a deep breath that exceeded the set V Te (see end of fig 4) ; (b) infants occasionally opposing inflation by tightening their abdominal muscles [CITATION_1] (this reduced and occasionally stopped some inflations); or (c) with interrupted expiration, the first part of the V Te was considerably less than the set V Te .",
